DLW-SPUN · the full weave of Lucifer

who   : The highest of the angels, fallen — Dis, Satan, the Emperor of the woeful realm.
what  : Three-faced and six-winged, frozen to the waist at the dead center of the Earth, weeping from six eyes and chewing the three arch-traitors — Judas, Brutus, Cassius — in his three mouths.
where : Circle IX — Judecca: the bottom of everything.
why   : He set himself against his Maker; his own beating wings freeze the lake that holds him fast.
when  : Since the first rebellion — forever.
how   : Not roaring but silent and mechanical — the absolute privation of good. And down his very body the travelers climb, and out, 'to see again the stars.'

class : Lucifer · the frozen center of the world
essence : lucifer.png
